# Brand voice (applies to all copy: pages, UI text, meta descriptions, blog)

- **British English** spelling and phrasing throughout (optimise, colour, centre, organisation).
- **Never use em dashes.** Restructure with commas, colons, brackets, or full stops instead.
- **Write plainly, like a knowledgeable human, not like AI.** Short, concrete, specific sentences. Say the real thing.
- **Ban the AI-tell and hype vocabulary** on the site: unlock, unleash, elevate, supercharge, seamless, seamlessly, leverage, game-changer, cutting-edge, revolutionise, robust, dive in, delve, "in today's fast-paced world", "we've got you covered", "the world of", "when it comes to". If a sentence could open any company's page, rewrite it to be specific to this one.
- No emoji in body copy unless it is a deliberate brand choice.
- Lead with the point. State the benefit or fact first, then support it.

This applies to code too: comments, button labels, error messages, and alt text follow the same voice.
